DANGCEM_Unknown_ceo_review_17_0,DANGCEM,DANGCEM,Industrial,Unknown,manual_pdf,ceo_review,"Items included in the financial statements of the Company are measured using the currency of the primary economic environment in which the entity operates ('the functional currency'). The functional currency and presentation currency of the Company is the Nigerian NGN (N) has been rounded to the nearest thousand ((NGN thousands)), unless otherwise stated.

A foreign currency transaction is recorded, on initial recognition in NGN, by applying to the foreign currency amount the spot exchange rate between the functional currency and the foreign currency at the date of the transaction.",89,poor,,,,,,,,pending
DANGCEM_Unknown_ceo_review_18_0,DANGCEM,DANGCEM,Industrial,Unknown,manual_pdf,ceo_review,"A foreign currency transaction is recorded, on initial recognition in NGN, by applying to the foreign currency amount the spot exchange rate between the functional currency and the foreign currency at the date of the transaction.

 non-monetary items that are measured in terms of historical cost in a foreign currency are translated using the exchange rate at the date of the transaction; and  non-monetary items that are measured at fair value in a foreign currency are translated using the exchange rates at the date when the fair value was determined.",92,poor,,,,,,,,pending
DANGCEM_Unknown_ceo_review_19_0,DANGCEM,DANGCEM,Industrial,Unknown,manual_pdf,ceo_review," non-monetary items that are measured in terms of historical cost in a foreign currency are translated using the exchange rate at the date of the transaction; and  non-monetary items that are measured at fair value in a foreign currency are translated using the exchange rates at the date when the fair value was determined.

