ETI_Unknown_outlook_2_0,ETI,ETI,Banking,Unknown,manual_pdf,outlook,"Net revenue increased by $188 million, or 28% (29% in constant currency), to $849 million. Net interest income increased by $82 million, or 22%, to $462 million, driven by growth in lending across business lines and higher trade loans in the commercial sector. Higher funding costs partially offset this growth. Non-interest revenues increased by $106 million, or 38%, to $387 million, primarily due to increased fees from client-driven foreign currency sales in Commercial banking, higher card and deposit-related fees from an increase in transaction volumes in the Consumer business.",89,acceptable,,,,,,,,pending
