ETI_Unknown_ceo_review_27_0,ETI,ETI,Banking,Unknown,manual_pdf,ceo_review,"Kingdom, United Arab Emirates and China, helping clients connect African opportunities to global trade and capital flows. Our network is one of our greatest strengths, not just because of its scale, but because of what it allows customers and clients to do: receive, save and move money, make payments, manage liquidity, finance trade and grow across borders.

What matters to us is not just growth, but the quality and durability of that growth. Our revenue base is broader and more balanced than before. In 2025, 42.4% of Group revenue came from non-interest revenue, while net fee and commission income accounted for 24.4% of net revenue. Net interest income increased to $1.4 billion, while non-interest revenue rose to $1.0 billion. Fee and commission income increased to $676 million. That tells us performance is being supported not only by lending, but also by payments, transaction services, treasury solutions and other fee-based activities across the franchise.",153,good,,,,,,,,pending
