ETI_Unknown_ceo_review_29_0,ETI,ETI,Banking,Unknown,manual_pdf,ceo_review,"Customer deposits grew by 24%, reaching $25.3 billion, marking the fastest growth in over a decade. Most significantly, low-cost and stable current and savings accounts (CASA) now account for 87.1% of total customer deposits, thereby improving the quality of our funding base and lowering its cost. Gross loans increased by 22% to $12.8 billion, supported by trade finance, digitally enabled consumer lending and focused client activity in areas where we see attractive returns and strong demand. Total assets rose by 23% to $34.5 billion and total equity increased 27% to $2.9 billion. For shareholders, that supports a more durable earnings profile and a stronger platform for sustained returns over time.",110,acceptable,,,,,,,,pending
