ETI_Unknown_ceo_review_32_0,ETI,ETI,Banking,Unknown,manual_pdf,ceo_review,"What matters is not only where those ratios ended the year, but how we managed towards them. We have become more disciplined in how we allocate capital, how we assess returns and where we choose to compete. We use return metrics more actively in our scorecards. We direct resources more deliberately to the businesses and markets where we see the strongest potential. And we are prepared to make difficult decisions where returns do not justify continued capital commitment.

A clear example of our commitment to capital discipline was our decision to divest the Mozambique business because it did not meet our performance and return criteria in a competitive market. For us, capital discipline is not a side topic; it is central to ensuring that growth translates into shareholder value.",129,acceptable,,,,,,,,pending
