ETI_Unknown_ceo_review_43_0,ETI,ETI,Banking,Unknown,manual_pdf,ceo_review,"Our regional performance also showed the value of diversification. UEMOA, AWA and CESA all delivered strong revenue growth and healthy returns on equity. UEMOA remained strong, with profit before tax rising 11% (+6% in constant currency) and return on equity of 26.8%. AWA delivered profit before tax growth of 28% (+18% in constant currency), with good momentum across both business lines.

CESA, our fastest growing and highest performing region, recorded profit before tax growth of 52% (+50% in constant currency) and return on equity of 36.1%. Our Nigeria affiliate grew its revenues by 22% (+28% in constant currency) and pre-provision profit by 96% (+113% in constant currency), however, this was offset by necessary impairment provisions which impacted its profits and returns. Our broad-based performance in other regions helped offset weaker performance in Nigeria and again showed the strength of our regional footprint.",142,acceptable,,,,,,,,pending
