Our Returns pillar focuses on having a disciplined approach to capital management and allocation, converting our scale, network and capabilities into stronger and more sustainable shareholder value. In particular, we have focused on and made significant progress on dividend upstreaming by subsidiaries, which has grown from $217 million in 2024 to $303 million in 2025. This has strengthened our central liquidity and capital position, supporting our proposed dividend payment.",133,good,,,,,,,,pending
ETI_Unknown_ceo_review_57_0,ETI,ETI,Banking,Unknown,manual_pdf,ceo_review,"Our Returns pillar focuses on having a disciplined approach to capital management and allocation, converting our scale, network and capabilities into stronger and more sustainable shareholder value. In particular, we have focused on and made significant progress on dividend upstreaming by subsidiaries, which has grown from $217 million in 2024 to $303 million in 2025. This has strengthened our central liquidity and capital position, supporting our proposed dividend payment.

In 2025, we made progress across all three areas. We improved our payments, cash management and trade finance capabilities. We continued to invest in technology and digital platforms to support faster product delivery, better integration across markets and a stronger customer experience. We also took steps to improve how the Group works internally, simplifying processes, strengthening governance and making execution more disciplined. Across the Group, we remained focused on doing the simple things well, with consistency, accountability and better followthrough. We are not getting distracted; we are taking the right difficult decisions and executing with agility and discipline.",167,good,,,,,,,,pending
