ETI_Unknown_ceo_review_59_0,ETI,ETI,Banking,Unknown,manual_pdf,ceo_review,"Ecobank Foundation, we continued to support social impact across Africa, with programmes focused on health, education and gender equality. In 2025, the Foundation strengthened its role as a platform for partnerships, including work on health and nutrition, inclusive digital education, and women's financial empowerment. This reflects a simple belief: stronger communities help build stronger economies.

In education, the Foundation concluded its three-year ""Transforming Africa Through Education"" campaign, exceeding its initial targets by establishing 66 IT laboratories and training 46,414 children and young people across the continent. Through the enhanced Ellevate programme, launched in nine African countries in March 2025, Ecobank also continued to support women entrepreneurs with financing, mentoring and advisory services. These initiatives are part of how the Group connects financial inclusion with broader economic inclusion.",127,good,,,,,,,,pending
