NB_2023_outlook_25_0,NB,Nigerian Breweries Plc,Consumer Goods,2023,annual_report,outlook,"234 Stores Limited was incorporated on November 7, 2018, as a subsidiary to explore opportunities in the route- to-market and became fully operational in 2020. As previously reported, the operations of the subsidiary were discontinued in 2024. The formal winding up process for the company is currently underway and is expected to be completed in accordance with the regulatory requirements for the dissolution of subsidiaries.

The Company recorded a rebound in 2025 after a difficult and challenging 2024 due to the impact of macroeconomic factors. The Company recorded a strong performance in 2025 and completed the acquisition of Distell Wines and Spirits Nigeria Limited (""Distell""). Group revenue rose to a historic N1.47 trillion, a 36% increase driven by appropriate pricing and increased competitiveness. Group operating profit rose to N205 billion reflecting a consistently strong internal efficiency. Group net profit rebounded to N99 billion, reversing the prior year's loss. This rebound was supported by a reduction in net finance charges by",160,good,,,,,,,,pending
