WAPCO_Unknown_outlook_0_0,WAPCO,WAPCO,Industrial,Unknown,manual_pdf,outlook,"Looking ahead, we remain confident in the long-term fundamentals of Nigeria's infrastructure and construction sector. The country's significant infrastructure deficit, rapid urbanization, and continued demand for housing and transportation networks present substantial opportunities for sustained growth in the building materials industry.

While short-term macroeconomic headwinds may persist, including energy cost pressures and broader global uncertainties, the longterm outlook for the sector remains compelling. Ongoing investments in infrastructure development, urban expansion, and public-private sector collaboration are expected to continue supporting demand for cement and innovative building solutions across the country.",89,good,,,,,,,,pending
WAPCO_Unknown_outlook_1_0,WAPCO,WAPCO,Industrial,Unknown,manual_pdf,outlook,"While short-term macroeconomic headwinds may persist, including energy cost pressures and broader global uncertainties, the longterm outlook for the sector remains compelling. Ongoing investments in infrastructure development, urban expansion, and public-private sector collaboration are expected to continue supporting demand for cement and innovative building solutions across the country.

Lafarge Africa Plc remains well positioned to capitalize on these opportunities. Our strategic priorities will continue to focus on strengthening operational efficiency, accelerating product innovation, expanding our portfolio of sustainable building solutions, and enhancing customer value through superior service and quality.",89,acceptable,,,,,,,,pending
WAPCO_Unknown_outlook_2_0,WAPCO,WAPCO,Industrial,Unknown,manual_pdf,outlook,"Lafarge Africa Plc remains well positioned to capitalize on these opportunities. Our strategic priorities will continue to focus on strengthening operational efficiency, accelerating product innovation, expanding our portfolio of sustainable building solutions, and enhancing customer value through superior service and quality.

Innovation and sustainability will remain central to our strategy as we continue to develop products and solutions that support a lower-carbon built environment while meeting the evolving needs of our customers.",72,acceptable,,,,,,,,pending
WAPCO_Unknown_outlook_3_0,WAPCO,WAPCO,Industrial,Unknown,manual_pdf,outlook,"Innovation and sustainability will remain central to our strategy as we continue to develop products and solutions that support a lower-carbon built environment while meeting the evolving needs of our customers.

In closing, I would like to express my sincere appreciation to my fellow members of the Board for their continued guidance and stewardship, as well as to our management team and employees whose dedication, professionalism, and resilience have been instrumental in delivering the strong performance recorded during the year. I also extend my gratitude to our customers, business partners, regulators, and the communities in which we operate for their continued collaboration and support. Most importantly, I thank our valued shareholders for the trust and confidence you continue to place in Lafarge Africa Plc.",124,good,,,,,,,,pending
WAPCO_Unknown_outlook_4_0,WAPCO,WAPCO,Industrial,Unknown,manual_pdf,outlook,"In closing, I would like to express my sincere appreciation to my fellow members of the Board for their continued guidance and stewardship, as well as to our management team and employees whose dedication, professionalism, and resilience have been instrumental in delivering the strong performance recorded during the year. I also extend my gratitude to our customers, business partners, regulators, and the communities in which we operate for their continued collaboration and support. Most importantly, I thank our valued shareholders for the trust and confidence you continue to place in Lafarge Africa Plc.",93,good,,,,,,,,pending
WAPCO_Unknown_outlook_5_0,WAPCO,WAPCO,Industrial,Unknown,manual_pdf,outlook,"As we look to the future, we remain firmly committed to strengthening our leadership in the building solutions sector through operational excellence, innovation, and sustainability. Guided by our strategic priorities and supported by the strength of our people and partnerships, we are confident in our ability to navigate the evolving business landscape and continue creating sustainable long-term value for all stakeholders.

On behalf of the Board, I thank you for your continued support and engagement, and I look forward to your active participation during the proceedings of this 67th Annual General Meeting.",92,acceptable,,,,,,,,pending
WAPCO_Unknown_outlook_6_0,WAPCO,WAPCO,Industrial,Unknown,manual_pdf,outlook,"On behalf of the Board, I thank you for your continued support and engagement, and I look forward to your active participation during the proceedings of this 67th Annual General Meeting.

Chairman that come with it. Our ambition is to contribute meaningfully to Nigeria's infrastructure and housing development while advancing solutions that promote a lower-carbon and more sustainable built environment.",60,poor,,,,,,,,pending
WAPCO_Unknown_outlook_8_0,WAPCO,WAPCO,Industrial,Unknown,manual_pdf,outlook,"During the year under review, we intensified our decarbonization efforts and continued to strengthen the sustainability foundations of our business. Significant progress was made through increased investment in alternative fuel systems across our plants, enabling us to reduce reliance on traditional fossil fuels and lower the carbon intensity of our operations. In addition, the Company expanded its logistics modernization program with the introduction of over 500 energy-efficient trucks, improving both fuel efficiency and operational performance across our distribution network.

We also deepened our collaboration with public sector partners, including our partnership with the Lagos State Government on waste-to-energy initiatives, which supports the circular economy by converting municipal waste into alternative fuel for cement production.",114,good,,,,,,,,pending
WAPCO_Unknown_outlook_9_0,WAPCO,WAPCO,Industrial,Unknown,manual_pdf,outlook,"We also deepened our collaboration with public sector partners, including our partnership with the Lagos State Government on waste-to-energy initiatives, which supports the circular economy by converting municipal waste into alternative fuel for cement production.

Through these initiatives, we continue to promote responsible resource management while reducing environmental impact across our operations. Beyond environmental performance, Lafarge Africa maintains an unwavering commitment to health and safety, which remains a core priority across all our sites. We continue to strengthen our safety culture, implement rigorous operational standards, and invest in training and systems that protect the wellbeing of our employees, contractors, and partners.",101,acceptable,,,,,,,,pending
WAPCO_Unknown_outlook_10_0,WAPCO,WAPCO,Industrial,Unknown,manual_pdf,outlook,"Through these initiatives, we continue to promote responsible resource management while reducing environmental impact across our operations. Beyond environmental performance, Lafarge Africa maintains an unwavering commitment to health and safety, which remains a core priority across all our sites. We continue to strengthen our safety culture, implement rigorous operational standards, and invest in training and systems that protect the wellbeing of our employees, contractors, and partners.

Our sustainability commitment extends beyond environmental stewardship to fostering inclusive social development in the communities where we operate. During 2025, the Company implemented 128 corporate social responsibility initiatives, reaching more than 122,000 beneficiaries across and beyond our five host communities - Lagos, Ashaka, Mfamosing, Ewekoro, and Sagamu.",113,good,,,,,,,,pending
WAPCO_Unknown_outlook_11_0,WAPCO,WAPCO,Industrial,Unknown,manual_pdf,outlook,"Our sustainability commitment extends beyond environmental stewardship to fostering inclusive social development in the communities where we operate. During 2025, the Company implemented 128 corporate social responsibility initiatives, reaching more than 122,000 beneficiaries across and beyond our five host communities - Lagos, Ashaka, Mfamosing, Ewekoro, and Sagamu.

These initiatives focused on community development, education, healthcare, skills empowerment, and infrastructure support, reflecting our dedication to creating shared value for society.",69,acceptable,,,,,,,,pending
